--- log ---
2026-05-03T15:00Z claude created
2026-05-03T16:00Z claude status closed — already-done: superseded by PR #85 (commit aa7e40e), which mechanized /ticket-close to delegate to `erg close <id> <reason>`. The reason-argument feature this ticket asked for is already on main; argument-hint reads `<ticket-id> [reason]`. PR #85 also addressed the broader 0057 vision (route mutations through erg binary) for the close path.

--- body ---
## Context

The `/ticket-close` skill currently takes only `<ticket-id>` (per its
frontmatter `argument-hint: <ticket-id>`). The body of the skill at
step 2 says "Append log line: `{timestamp} {agent} status closed — {reason}`",
but there is no mechanism for the caller to *supply* the reason — it
ends up baked into whatever the closing agent decides to write at that
moment.

This came up during the 2026-05-03 mecanisation raid (PR #89, Tier 2 of
ticket 0049). Pick-ticket needs to close a ticket whose exit criteria
are already met and explicitly signal the reason as `already-done` so
that downstream tooling (audit scripts, future Tier 1 housekeeping)
can grep `sweep-close: already-done` to distinguish self-closures from
human-driven closures. Because `/ticket-close <id>` cannot accept a
reason, pick-ticket now writes its own
`{ts} claude note sweep-close: already-done hash:<bodyhash>` log line
*after* calling `/ticket-close`, which is a layering wart: pick-ticket
and ticket-close together know how to "close with reason" but the
structured-reason bit lives only in pick-ticket prose.

## Goal

Allow `/ticket-close <id> <reason>` to set the structured reason in the
status log line directly, so pick-ticket (and any future caller) can
delegate the full close+annotate operation in one call.

## Actions

1. Update `skills/ticket-close/SKILL.md`:
   - Frontmatter: `argument-hint: <ticket-id> [reason]`
   - Step 1: parse `$ARGUMENTS` into ticket-id (first whitespace-separated
     token) and optional reason (rest of the string).
   - Step 2: append `{timestamp} {agent} status closed — {reason}`
     where `{reason}` is the parsed reason if non-empty, else a default
     like `closed by /ticket-close`.

2. Update `skills/pick-ticket/SKILL.md` step 4 (the lightweight
   exit-criteria check added in PR #89): replace the two-step
   `/ticket-close <id>` + manual `sweep-close: already-done` log line
   with a single `/ticket-close <id> already-done`. The log line then
   reads `{ts} claude status closed — already-done`, which serves the
   same audit purpose as the current `sweep-close: already-done` line.

3. Update any tests that grep for `sweep-close: already-done` to grep
   for `status closed — already-done` instead, OR keep the
   `sweep-close:` convention and have ticket-close emit BOTH a `status`
   line and a `sweep-close:` line when called with `already-done`.
   Decide which convention to keep before implementing.

## Test

Add a small bash test under `tests/`:
- `tests/test_ticket_close_reason.sh`
- Create a temp `.erg` ticket file in a fixture dir.
- Invoke whatever wraps `/ticket-close` non-interactively (a small shell
  helper, or a direct file-mutation function if `/ticket-close` itself
  is LLM-only) with id + reason.
- Assert the resulting log line matches the expected pattern and that
  the body hash is present if the caller is `pick-ticket`.

## Exit criteria

- `/ticket-close <id> <reason>` writes a status log line that includes
  the reason in a grep-stable form.
- `/ticket-close <id>` (no reason) still works and writes a default
  reason.
- PR #89's pick-ticket step 4 prose can be simplified to call
  `/ticket-close <id> already-done` and remove its hand-written log
  line.
- Existing audit / tooling that greps for `already-done` continues to
  match.

## Notes

This is small (probably <30 lines of skill prose). Spawned out of the
mecanisation raid Phase 6/7 review — see
`docs/2026-05-03-raid-mecanisation-phase6-7.md` §4.
